This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Performance (cs.PF) sub-categories, as it deals with the concept of performance portability in computing. It may also be relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category, as well as the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories, as achieving performance portability often involves considerations of software design and hardware architecture.
